title: Victorian Novelists
description: Intended for the general reader rather than the literary specialist, this 1899 collection of essays begins with notes on the novel as an art-form. The author then considers the lives and works of Sir Walter Scott, Jane Austen, Charles Dickens, William Makepeace Thackeray, Charlotte Bronte, George Eliot, George Meredith, and others.
author: James Oliphant
